    "Ronald McAulay owns a large stake in CLP Holdings, the power company chaired by brother-in-law Michael Kadoorie.",
    "He also has a stake in the Hongkong and Shanghai Hotels, which operates the famous Peninsula Hotel in Hong Kong and London.",
    "He resigned from the board of the former in 2016 and the latter in 2017 after decades of service.",
    "His son, Andrew, is chairman of Kadoorie Farm & Botanic Garden in the New Territories."
  ],
  "about": [
    "McAulay is a member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Scotland. He is also an honorary trustee of the Tate Foundation in London."
  ]
